1
00:00:01,510 --> 00:00:03,940
(Episode 2)

2
00:00:03,940 --> 00:00:05,240
(Receive your punishment.)

3
00:00:07,110 --> 00:00:08,210
Receive your punishment.

4
00:00:09,779 --> 00:00:10,779
Receive...

5
00:00:11,720 --> 00:00:12,849
Receive your punishment.

6
00:00:13,990 --> 00:00:15,189
Get this instead.

7
00:00:19,489 --> 00:00:20,960
I found my clothes.

8
00:00:21,030 --> 00:00:23,429
The guys from Exit Three Gang...

9
00:00:23,429 --> 00:00:25,530
sent this package
by express delivery.

10
00:00:27,100 --> 00:00:30,140
We can invoice that, can't we?

11
00:00:31,600 --> 00:00:33,710
How can you sleep in this situation?

12
00:00:35,909 --> 00:00:38,210
Look. A police officer...

13
00:00:38,210 --> 00:00:39,640
was disgraced on the street.

14
00:00:39,939 --> 00:00:41,710
Who printed this out?

15
00:00:43,310 --> 00:00:44,579
It's so big.

16
00:00:50,460 --> 00:00:53,359
Is there anything you want
to say to the viewers?

17
00:00:53,630 --> 00:00:56,490
Dear viewers
and the citizens of Gudam,

18
00:00:56,759 --> 00:00:58,929
I, the head of Gudam office,

19
00:00:59,030 --> 00:01:01,130
will make Gudam a place...

20
00:01:01,130 --> 00:01:03,500
where everyone wants to live in...

21
00:01:03,500 --> 00:01:04,799
and where everyone feels safe.

22
00:01:05,099 --> 00:01:06,340
Please support me.

23
00:01:06,540 --> 00:01:09,010
All right. Gudam placed first...

24
00:01:09,010 --> 00:01:10,840
in the categories of welfare,
public order, and economy...

25
00:01:10,840 --> 00:01:12,939
on the evaluation
of regions in Seoul.

26
00:01:12,939 --> 00:01:14,379
She's the hardest
working person in Gudam.

27
00:01:14,379 --> 00:01:16,549
This was an interview with the head
of Gudam Office, Jeong Dong Ja.

28
00:01:16,879 --> 00:01:18,950
Cut. Good work, everyone.

29
00:01:19,219 --> 00:01:20,989
- Good work.
- Good work.

30
00:01:20,989 --> 00:01:21,989
It's done.

31
00:01:25,090 --> 00:01:27,359
You look so good on the screen.

32
00:01:27,359 --> 00:01:28,859
Didn't I seem too tough?

33
00:01:28,859 --> 00:01:30,329
- No, no.
- Was it okay?

34
00:01:30,329 --> 00:01:31,430
You seemed tough,

35
00:01:31,530 --> 00:01:33,129
but you seemed humane as well.

36
00:01:34,099 --> 00:01:35,269
By the way,

37
00:01:37,170 --> 00:01:39,870
Is the site for the history museum
not settled yet?

38
00:01:40,239 --> 00:01:41,569
Everyone's asking about it.

39
00:01:42,739 --> 00:01:44,379
Have you not convinced
President Seo?

40
00:01:45,209 --> 00:01:47,349
I will finish it off today,
so don't worry.

41
00:01:47,349 --> 00:01:49,750
Then why are you taking time here?

42
00:01:49,810 --> 00:01:51,219
Go finish it.

43
00:01:51,620 --> 00:01:53,519
Okay, I got it.

44
00:01:54,549 --> 00:01:56,290
Let me feed those old people first.

45
00:01:56,859 --> 00:01:58,290
Goodness.

46
00:01:58,959 --> 00:02:03,030
(A salubrious and crime-free city)

47
00:02:15,110 --> 00:02:16,840
A petition urging to investigate
without sanctuary...

48
00:02:16,840 --> 00:02:18,110
has been made to the Blue House.

49
00:02:19,080 --> 00:02:20,409
Hear me out.

50
00:02:20,610 --> 00:02:23,349
Is the law a joke?

51
00:02:24,020 --> 00:02:26,180
If we don't listen to them,
they say we're wrong.

52
00:02:26,949 --> 00:02:29,419
Gosh, they're so uncivilized.

53
00:02:29,419 --> 00:02:32,259
Then are you saying that
your judgment is correct?

54
00:02:32,419 --> 00:02:35,090
Yes. I believe I am just.

55
00:02:35,629 --> 00:02:37,129
One more question, ma'am.

56
00:02:37,500 --> 00:02:38,629
Enough!

57
00:02:39,099 --> 00:02:41,699
This is the true nature
of the prosecution.

58
00:02:42,229 --> 00:02:44,270
This was Oh Bo Young of UBS News.

59
00:02:46,199 --> 00:02:47,469
Hey!

60
00:02:48,539 --> 00:02:51,080
Talk properly, you jerk.

61
00:02:51,409 --> 00:02:54,009
Say, "She sells seashells
by the seashore."

62
00:02:57,080 --> 00:02:58,080
Sleep with me?

63
00:03:01,490 --> 00:03:02,819
This jerk...

64
00:03:02,819 --> 00:03:04,819
- still doesn't get it.
- They're doing it again.

65
00:03:06,259 --> 00:03:08,229
- It's because he's ugly.
- Goodness.

66
00:03:08,590 --> 00:03:11,360
Come on, now. He's a foreigner.
Cut him some slack.

67
00:03:11,599 --> 00:03:13,969
If he wants to make money here,
shouldn't he speak our language?

68
00:03:14,370 --> 00:03:15,770
Am I right?

69
00:03:16,300 --> 00:03:17,340
What?

70
00:03:17,539 --> 00:03:19,099
- Answer me.
- Sir.

71
00:03:24,639 --> 00:03:27,080
- There you go again.
- He's my Thai friend.

72
00:03:27,509 --> 00:03:29,479
Hey, he's a Korean police officer.

73
00:03:30,210 --> 00:03:32,250
- Hello.
- I'll see you around.

74
00:03:33,750 --> 00:03:35,020
Goodbye.

75
00:03:35,090 --> 00:03:36,120
Goodbye, sir.

76
00:03:40,889 --> 00:03:42,560
Eat up.

77
00:03:42,560 --> 00:03:44,830
Here, have some of this.

78
00:03:44,830 --> 00:03:45,900
Thank you.

79
00:03:46,530 --> 00:03:48,069
- It's good.
- Is he doing well?

80
00:03:48,069 --> 00:03:49,169
- Yes.
- I see.

81
00:03:50,030 --> 00:03:52,740
- Thank you so much.
- My pleasure. Have more.

82
00:03:52,740 --> 00:03:54,639
Have some of this. Hello.

83
00:03:54,939 --> 00:03:56,210
President Seo is here.

84
00:04:03,310 --> 00:04:04,449
- Hello, sir.
- Hello, sir.

85
00:04:05,580 --> 00:04:06,580
Get out.

86
00:04:08,590 --> 00:04:09,949
Darn it.

87
00:04:10,860 --> 00:04:11,919
Sit down.

88
00:04:15,360 --> 00:04:16,360
President Seo.

89
00:04:18,829 --> 00:04:22,870
Was the price I asked
for that land unreasonable?

90
00:04:24,540 --> 00:04:27,610
Was it? I believe I offered you
a reasonable price.

91
00:04:27,740 --> 00:04:29,709
So why aren't you listening to me?

92
00:04:30,139 --> 00:04:31,740
Well...

93
00:04:32,980 --> 00:04:34,579
The value differs
for every institution...

94
00:04:34,579 --> 00:04:36,509
Darn it. What are you saying?

95
00:04:36,879 --> 00:04:40,490
Why can't Koreans get it
when we speak nicely?

96
00:04:40,850 --> 00:04:41,889
Why?

97
00:04:42,250 --> 00:04:44,689
Shouldn't we be reasonable?

98
00:04:45,160 --> 00:04:47,529
Let's talk this out through
common sense and reasoning.

99
00:04:48,889 --> 00:04:51,199
- All right.
- You understand me, right?

100
00:04:51,629 --> 00:04:52,860
I trust that you do.

101
00:04:53,930 --> 00:04:55,069
Why aren't you answering?

102
00:04:55,629 --> 00:04:56,670
Okay.

103
00:04:59,670 --> 00:05:01,470
You better not go back on your word.

104
00:05:03,569 --> 00:05:04,639
Mr. Hwang.

105
00:05:06,980 --> 00:05:09,610
Could you please give me
some time to consider this?

106
00:05:13,850 --> 00:05:15,720
Did you say, time?

107
00:05:17,189 --> 00:05:19,519
He just won't do.

108
00:05:20,860 --> 00:05:23,699
Let's go back to the good, old days.

109
00:05:27,470 --> 00:05:29,500
Hold still, please.

110
00:05:35,370 --> 00:05:37,680
Who's our special guest...

111
00:05:37,680 --> 00:05:40,139
who has made Father Lee
so happy from the early morning?

112
00:05:40,139 --> 00:05:41,579
He's from a Yeosu diocese.

113
00:05:41,649 --> 00:05:42,910
He's Father Lee's former pupil.

114
00:05:43,509 --> 00:05:44,819
Is he not officially appointed?

115
00:05:44,819 --> 00:05:46,649
No, he'll be here as a guest.

116
00:05:46,649 --> 00:05:48,019
Please carry these.

117
00:05:48,620 --> 00:05:49,889
Goodness.

118
00:05:50,050 --> 00:05:52,920
- You bought so much.
- Goodness.

119
00:05:53,420 --> 00:05:56,660
I'll do all the cooking today,

120
00:05:56,660 --> 00:05:58,930
so don't try to help me.

121
00:05:59,199 --> 00:06:01,000
Hello, Father.

122
00:06:10,439 --> 00:06:13,680
My brothers,
to what do I owe the pleasure?

123
00:06:14,079 --> 00:06:16,180
What do you think?
You already know.

124
00:06:18,319 --> 00:06:20,079
It's about that again?

125
00:06:20,079 --> 00:06:22,689
My thoughts on that haven't changed,

126
00:06:22,689 --> 00:06:24,120
so please tell your president so.

127
00:06:24,120 --> 00:06:26,759
Oh, right. Would you like
to have some snacks?

128
00:06:26,959 --> 00:06:29,389
Gosh, you're irritating me.

129
00:06:29,389 --> 00:06:32,660
- You better listen to me.
- Please watch what you say.

130
00:06:33,259 --> 00:06:34,269
Look at that.

131
00:06:35,329 --> 00:06:38,040
The Holy Spirit is talking
through him. Am I right?

132
00:06:38,870 --> 00:06:41,269
Wait. Wait!

133
00:06:41,410 --> 00:06:43,879
If you keep doing this,
I'll call the police.

134
00:06:43,879 --> 00:06:45,379
Do that.

135
00:06:45,980 --> 00:06:49,250
Please don't be like this,
and come have some snacks.

136
00:06:50,279 --> 00:06:51,649
I don't like snacks...

137
00:06:51,850 --> 00:06:54,350
because they get stuck
in between my teeth.

138
00:06:54,420 --> 00:06:56,350
I'll be visiting here every day
from now on, okay?

139
00:07:04,829 --> 00:07:07,170
(Daebum Trading)

140
00:07:07,170 --> 00:07:08,670
- Hey.
- Yes?

141
00:07:09,069 --> 00:07:10,370
You've been here for so long,

142
00:07:10,370 --> 00:07:12,199
so why are you still bad
at adjusting the water level?

143
00:07:12,569 --> 00:07:14,009
Should I bring more water?

144
00:07:14,540 --> 00:07:16,170
Is this Pyeongyang naengmyeon?

145
00:07:16,569 --> 00:07:18,579
- Get out. Leave.
- I'm sorry, sir.

146
00:07:21,680 --> 00:07:23,050
How's President Seo doing?

147
00:07:23,050 --> 00:07:25,420
He has a few cuts,
but his brain is undamaged.

148
00:07:26,949 --> 00:07:28,250
I guess his head's doing fine.

149
00:07:28,949 --> 00:07:30,389
Go get his seal on the contract.

150
00:07:30,389 --> 00:07:32,220
- He'll give it right away.
- Yes, sir.

151
00:07:32,490 --> 00:07:33,519
Good.

152
00:07:34,029 --> 00:07:36,230
Did Jang Ryong visit the cathedral?

153
00:07:36,230 --> 00:07:37,230
He did.

154
00:07:37,660 --> 00:07:39,360
You need to pressure them
night and day.

155
00:07:39,800 --> 00:07:41,769
- We don't have much time.
- Yes, sir.

156
00:07:41,769 --> 00:07:42,829
All right.

157
00:07:45,100 --> 00:07:46,269
This tastes disgusting.

158
00:08:08,529 --> 00:08:09,560
I'm here.

159
00:08:14,870 --> 00:08:16,870
I'm happy you came.

160
00:08:18,800 --> 00:08:21,709
Are you not eating well?
Why are you so frail?

161
00:08:22,069 --> 00:08:24,480
If you want to look cool,
you need to be slim.

162
00:08:26,910 --> 00:08:28,009
Let's go in and eat.

163
00:08:28,009 --> 00:08:31,050
I made seaweed soup
and boiled beef, your favorites.

164
00:08:31,350 --> 00:08:34,250
Don't make it sound like I came
back home after giving birth.

165
00:08:35,750 --> 00:08:36,820
Let's go.

166
00:08:38,720 --> 00:08:40,860
In Jesus' name we pray,

167
00:08:41,490 --> 00:08:42,759
- amen.
- Amen.

168
00:08:43,289 --> 00:08:45,230
- In the Father, the Son...
- In the Father, the Son...

169
00:08:45,700 --> 00:08:46,700
- Amen.
- Amen.

170
00:08:48,429 --> 00:08:51,139
You must be close to Father Lee.

171
00:08:51,799 --> 00:08:52,799
Yes.

172
00:08:52,799 --> 00:08:54,870
How long have you two
known each other?

173
00:08:54,940 --> 00:08:56,769
- Since a long time ago.
- I see.

174
00:08:56,769 --> 00:08:58,179
How long ago?

175
00:09:00,480 --> 00:09:01,580
A very long time ago.

176
00:09:02,210 --> 00:09:04,450
- That means...
- You should eat.

177
00:09:04,779 --> 00:09:05,820
All right.

178
00:09:06,320 --> 00:09:08,490
What brings you here
from Yeosu?

179
00:09:08,490 --> 00:09:09,620
- Sister.
- Yes?

180
00:09:09,620 --> 00:09:11,690
- Let's eat first.
- Okay.

181
00:09:14,190 --> 00:09:15,429
I caused trouble there.

182
00:09:17,360 --> 00:09:19,799
I beat a believer and his underling
to a pulp.

183
00:09:20,830 --> 00:09:23,200
I heard one of them
still can't close his mouth.

184
00:09:33,110 --> 00:09:34,580
I'm sorry.

185
00:09:36,509 --> 00:09:38,149
Goodness.

186
00:09:38,750 --> 00:09:42,850
A priest shouldn't make such jokes.

187
00:09:44,190 --> 00:09:45,259
It's not a joke.

188
00:09:49,129 --> 00:09:50,159
I'm not kidding.

189
00:09:51,360 --> 00:09:54,330
Come on, let's eat first.

190
00:10:02,039 --> 00:10:06,009
Father Lee prepared all of this
just for you,

191
00:10:06,009 --> 00:10:07,649
so you should eat up.

192
00:10:09,049 --> 00:10:12,019
I had a bowl of jajangmyeon
before coming here.

193
00:10:12,480 --> 00:10:13,480
I see.

194
00:10:14,389 --> 00:10:16,250
Why did you have it
if we're going to eat...

195
00:10:16,250 --> 00:10:17,690
Because I wanted to eat it!

196
00:10:19,559 --> 00:10:21,259
- Goodness.
- I'm so vexed.

197
00:10:21,259 --> 00:10:24,460
You didn't have to get
so angry with me.

198
00:10:24,460 --> 00:10:25,460
All right.

199
00:10:25,529 --> 00:10:28,870
Have some of this seasoned eggplant.

200
00:10:29,500 --> 00:10:30,570
I...

201
00:10:31,570 --> 00:10:33,440
I'll get up first.

202
00:10:33,440 --> 00:10:35,509
Father Kim.

203
00:10:35,639 --> 00:10:38,110
You should pray
after you finish eating.

204
00:10:38,110 --> 00:10:39,309
We can do that.

205
00:10:39,309 --> 00:10:41,149
Father Han,
please escort him to his room.

206
00:10:42,279 --> 00:10:44,320
- It's all right. I know this place.
- Still...

207
00:10:44,320 --> 00:10:46,850
This place isn't a maze, come on!

208
00:10:48,919 --> 00:10:49,950
Darn it.

209
00:10:56,889 --> 00:10:58,960
What's with his temper?

210
00:11:02,330 --> 00:11:04,500
With all due respect,

211
00:11:04,870 --> 00:11:06,399
before the ordination,

212
00:11:06,399 --> 00:11:08,539
you all receive
a personality test, right?

213
00:11:09,639 --> 00:11:10,669
Yes, we do.

214
00:11:11,309 --> 00:11:12,409
Why do you ask?

215
00:11:12,879 --> 00:11:15,809
Does Father Kim seem very strange?

216
00:11:17,149 --> 00:11:18,649
Well...

217
00:11:19,350 --> 00:11:22,289
He seems to be so quiet,
but then he suddenly...

218
00:11:24,659 --> 00:11:25,860
I'm sorry.

219
00:11:26,590 --> 00:11:29,129
It's not easy to be like that.

220
00:11:29,559 --> 00:11:31,960
Every now and then,
there are short-tempered priests.

221
00:11:32,860 --> 00:11:33,899
No.

222
00:11:34,669 --> 00:11:37,129
This is a different level
of anger...

223
00:11:37,129 --> 00:11:39,000
than the one we're familiar with.

224
00:11:39,340 --> 00:11:40,639
How do I put it?

225
00:11:41,110 --> 00:11:43,870
I sense a bit of madness in him.

226
00:11:54,090 --> 00:11:55,149
A minute.

227
00:12:00,590 --> 00:12:01,590
Hold on.

228
00:12:10,700 --> 00:12:11,740
You weren't sleeping?

229
00:12:12,570 --> 00:12:13,570
It's too early.

230
00:12:15,669 --> 00:12:16,809
Take it out.

231
00:12:17,509 --> 00:12:18,539
What?

232
00:12:19,080 --> 00:12:21,850
You were drinking. Look.

233
00:12:21,909 --> 00:12:24,320
I made your favorite appetizer,
so take it out.

234
00:12:25,279 --> 00:12:27,320
Can you see through walls now?

235
00:12:38,730 --> 00:12:39,799
Do you want some?

236
00:12:40,029 --> 00:12:42,269
Come on, that's yours.

237
00:12:43,299 --> 00:12:44,639
I brought mine.

238
00:12:49,039 --> 00:12:51,009
All right, I'll pour you some.

239
00:13:02,950 --> 00:13:03,950
It's good.

240
00:13:05,259 --> 00:13:07,990
You're allowed to have
two more glasses.

241
00:13:08,559 --> 00:13:10,759
You have to lead
the service tomorrow.

242
00:13:11,100 --> 00:13:12,100
Me?

243
00:13:12,100 --> 00:13:14,830
Help me out so that
I can rest at least a week.

244
00:13:14,830 --> 00:13:17,470
How could you put me to work
the moment I come here?

245
00:13:17,539 --> 00:13:19,440
Why do you think
I allowed you to come here?

246
00:13:20,769 --> 00:13:22,009
Give it to me.

247
00:13:26,009 --> 00:13:27,009
By the way,

248
00:13:28,279 --> 00:13:30,049
why aren't you asking
about what I did?

249
00:13:31,620 --> 00:13:33,279
It's not surprising.

250
00:13:34,049 --> 00:13:36,149
You were always a troublemaker.

251
00:13:38,889 --> 00:13:40,120
But still,

252
00:13:41,059 --> 00:13:43,230
I'm sure you heard
about my situation.

253
00:13:44,600 --> 00:13:45,730
Why did you accept me back here?

254
00:13:47,000 --> 00:13:51,299
Will you not accept
your sick son back home?

255
00:13:56,210 --> 00:14:00,110
You and I are linked spiritually.

256
00:14:01,350 --> 00:14:03,210
So wherever you go
and however it may be,

257
00:14:03,610 --> 00:14:05,049
we will always meet again.

258
00:14:06,519 --> 00:14:08,850
Goodness, I guess I'll have
to keep seeing you.

259
00:14:11,320 --> 00:14:13,820
Don't cause trouble,

260
00:14:14,960 --> 00:14:16,789
and don't get involved in anything.

261
00:14:17,289 --> 00:14:18,529
Live a quiet life.

262
00:14:20,600 --> 00:14:24,129
If you cause trouble,
it pains my spirit.

263
00:14:29,809 --> 00:14:32,039
Welcome, Sister.

264
00:14:33,639 --> 00:14:35,279
Welcome.

265
00:14:36,909 --> 00:14:38,080
- Hi.
- Hello.

266
00:14:40,419 --> 00:14:41,820
Go say hi.

267
00:14:43,049 --> 00:14:44,659
Welcome.

268
00:14:46,220 --> 00:14:48,360
Hello, Sister Angela.

269
00:14:48,360 --> 00:14:50,460
Hello, Father.

270
00:14:51,029 --> 00:14:53,629
Is that young priest new here?

271
00:14:54,129 --> 00:14:56,000
Yes. He'll only be here for a while.

272
00:14:57,070 --> 00:14:58,139
I'll see you later.

273
00:14:58,139 --> 00:14:59,269
Okay.

274
00:14:59,899 --> 00:15:01,669
- Welcome.
- Hello.

275
00:15:03,840 --> 00:15:06,679
Look at that face. He's cute.

276
00:15:13,879 --> 00:15:14,990
Hello.

277
00:15:17,450 --> 00:15:18,460
Go in.

278
00:15:21,190 --> 00:15:22,360
Hello.

279
00:15:33,539 --> 00:15:35,809
The Lord is with you all.

280
00:15:36,070 --> 00:15:38,879
- Please be here with us.
- Please be here with us.

281
00:15:39,840 --> 00:15:42,179
Today, I will be sharing
the gospel with you.

282
00:15:43,179 --> 00:15:46,779
- Please speak to us, dear Lord.
- Please speak to us, dear Lord.

283
00:15:48,149 --> 00:15:49,990
"Love your enemies..."

284
00:15:50,750 --> 00:15:53,490
"and pray for those
who persecute you,"

285
00:15:54,889 --> 00:15:59,029
