287
00:16:06,870 --> 00:16:10,370
How can we become
true children of God?

288
00:16:10,769 --> 00:16:12,710
That is a never-ending question
for us.

289
00:16:15,210 --> 00:16:17,580
The first step in becoming
the Lord's children is...

290
00:16:21,720 --> 00:16:24,919
The first step in becoming
the Lord's children is...

291
00:16:24,990 --> 00:16:26,490
by admitting our sins...

292
00:16:26,490 --> 00:16:27,519
Hey!

293
00:16:28,860 --> 00:16:31,059
You, over there. You.

294
00:16:31,330 --> 00:16:33,759
2, 4, 6, 8. You, in the 8th row,
holding that bread.

295
00:16:34,929 --> 00:16:35,929
Leave.

296
00:16:36,429 --> 00:16:38,100
How dare you munch during...

297
00:16:41,740 --> 00:16:42,909
Leave this instant.

298
00:16:58,220 --> 00:16:59,259
Pull.

299
00:17:00,019 --> 00:17:01,330
I said, pull.

300
00:17:11,769 --> 00:17:12,769
Okay.

301
00:17:13,339 --> 00:17:14,569
Where was I?

302
00:17:15,069 --> 00:17:17,140
I forgot! Darn it.

303
00:17:20,839 --> 00:17:21,880
Father.

304
00:17:35,529 --> 00:17:37,829
How can we become
true children of God?

305
00:17:37,960 --> 00:17:39,859
That is a never-ending question
for us.

306
00:17:40,500 --> 00:17:41,529
But...

307
00:17:44,230 --> 00:17:48,109
Why do you ask for forgiveness
only when you come to church?

308
00:17:49,170 --> 00:17:51,839
You should ask those you have
done wrong for forgiveness first.

309
00:17:52,009 --> 00:17:53,779
Don't say it half-heartedly.

310
00:17:53,839 --> 00:17:57,549
Make sure your apologies come
from deep down within your hearts.

311
00:17:58,049 --> 00:17:59,180
Go do that.

312
00:18:00,420 --> 00:18:03,819
Once they forgive you, then you can
ask God for forgiveness.

313
00:18:03,819 --> 00:18:06,289
You ask if we can do it for you?
No. Do you know why?

314
00:18:07,759 --> 00:18:09,589
Because we aren't the ones
who make the final decisions.

315
00:18:10,660 --> 00:18:12,160
We're the messengers.

316
00:18:20,200 --> 00:18:21,910
What's with his temper?

317
00:18:22,069 --> 00:18:24,339
How can we ask every single
one of them for forgiveness?

318
00:18:24,579 --> 00:18:27,309
If we don't do that, he's saying
that we can't confess our sins.

319
00:18:28,079 --> 00:18:29,309
It's so weird.

320
00:18:29,849 --> 00:18:31,650
- The priest is weird too.
- I know.

321
00:18:35,119 --> 00:18:36,619
- In the Father, the Son...
- In the Father, the Son...

322
00:18:36,619 --> 00:18:38,160
- and the Holy Spirit.
- and the Holy Spirit.

323
00:18:38,660 --> 00:18:39,960
- Amen.
- Amen.

324
00:18:42,230 --> 00:18:44,900
It's been three weeks
since my last confession.

325
00:18:47,160 --> 00:18:49,769
I've been chafing
at my colleagues...

326
00:18:50,500 --> 00:18:51,839
and even cursed.

327
00:18:52,200 --> 00:18:54,670
Did you apologize and ask them
for forgiveness?

328
00:18:54,809 --> 00:18:55,869
No.

329
00:18:55,970 --> 00:18:57,769
Sincerely ask them
for forgiveness first.

330
00:18:57,980 --> 00:18:59,039
You can go.

331
00:19:00,039 --> 00:19:02,210
Wait. Just like that?

332
00:19:02,750 --> 00:19:03,849
Yes.

333
00:19:04,180 --> 00:19:05,220
Father.

334
00:19:05,480 --> 00:19:07,220
Will you not read the scripture
or give me penance?

335
00:19:07,220 --> 00:19:10,150
No. Ask for their forgiveness first,
and then you may come back.

336
00:19:11,559 --> 00:19:12,589
But...

337
00:19:16,589 --> 00:19:17,759
Father.

338
00:19:20,700 --> 00:19:22,630
What was that back there?

339
00:19:26,970 --> 00:19:28,069
Is something the matter?

340
00:19:28,509 --> 00:19:31,480
Gosh, he looks
even more dazzling up-close.

341
00:19:33,880 --> 00:19:36,579
Isn't what you're doing
against canon law?

342
00:19:36,779 --> 00:19:38,680
I think a believer complaining
to a priest like this...

343
00:19:39,019 --> 00:19:40,319
is even more against it.

344
00:19:40,420 --> 00:19:43,220
You were the one who was being
insincere back there.

345
00:19:43,490 --> 00:19:45,190
I believe I was just.

346
00:19:45,660 --> 00:19:48,259
Yes. I believe I am just.

347
00:19:48,859 --> 00:19:50,259
One more question, ma'am.

348
00:19:50,789 --> 00:19:51,829
Enough!

349
00:19:51,829 --> 00:19:52,829
("The Prosecution Believes
They Are Just")

350
00:19:55,670 --> 00:19:56,829
Apologize.

351
00:19:56,829 --> 00:19:58,700
If not, I'm going to report this
to the diocese.

352
00:20:00,500 --> 00:20:01,970
Do that then.

353
00:20:02,569 --> 00:20:03,740
Do you know who I am?

354
00:20:04,039 --> 00:20:05,109
Goodness.

355
00:20:06,380 --> 00:20:07,410
Hey, old man.

356
00:20:08,380 --> 00:20:09,750
Are you dying to brag
that you're a prosecutor?

357
00:20:11,279 --> 00:20:13,849
I guess Father Lee already told you.

358
00:20:14,180 --> 00:20:15,720
No, I saw you on TV.

359
00:20:16,619 --> 00:20:17,619
This was your last image.

360
00:20:19,619 --> 00:20:21,019
Did you watch that?

361
00:20:21,089 --> 00:20:23,259
Except for that last part,
I looked pretty nice.

362
00:20:23,490 --> 00:20:25,660
Yes, your eyes looked nice,
old man.

363
00:20:26,430 --> 00:20:27,829
"Old man"?

364
00:20:27,829 --> 00:20:29,700
That's a lame, old joke.

365
00:20:30,599 --> 00:20:34,269
Many old men attend churches,
cathedrals, and temples.

366
00:20:34,299 --> 00:20:36,710
They pay hefty offerings
and commit hefty sins as well.

367
00:20:37,470 --> 00:20:39,880
But they just come to make
themselves feel better.

368
00:20:41,039 --> 00:20:44,150
They don't care about the people
whom they've hurt.

369
00:20:45,849 --> 00:20:48,490
Nobody is hurt because of me.

370
00:20:48,720 --> 00:20:49,849
Look, Sister.

371
00:20:50,150 --> 00:20:51,589
Drawing a cross on your forehead
with holy water...

372
00:20:51,589 --> 00:20:52,759
won't get you into heaven.

373
00:20:53,089 --> 00:20:55,230
Those who only attend services
so that they can sin in peace...

374
00:20:55,630 --> 00:20:57,529
won't go to heaven even if
they take a shower with holy water.

375
00:20:57,529 --> 00:20:58,529
Got that?

376
00:21:04,970 --> 00:21:07,099
I will let you off this time...

377
00:21:07,599 --> 00:21:09,970
since you're astonishingly handsome.

378
00:21:14,950 --> 00:21:16,480
She really knows how to press
my buttons.

379
00:21:24,319 --> 00:21:26,160
- Father.
- Yes?

380
00:21:27,220 --> 00:21:30,190
Father Lee wants you to greet
the children at the orphanage.

381
00:21:30,390 --> 00:21:32,829
He told them
that a new priest is here.

382
00:21:32,900 --> 00:21:34,259
He's exhilarated.

383
00:21:34,799 --> 00:21:36,000
He's making me do all the work.

384
00:21:40,869 --> 00:21:41,869
Keep it.

385
00:21:49,309 --> 00:21:53,049
Why are you paying so much donation?

386
00:21:53,049 --> 00:21:54,579
It's for you.

387
00:21:54,579 --> 00:21:56,089
You can use that money
to eat whatever you want.

388
00:22:00,390 --> 00:22:02,960
You're giving me this
to do you a favor, right?

389
00:22:03,490 --> 00:22:05,529
I'm just giving it for you to use.

390
00:22:05,529 --> 00:22:07,000
Take it back.

391
00:22:07,200 --> 00:22:09,769
Our church will take care
of the facility management.

392
00:22:11,769 --> 00:22:14,910
If you entrust me
with the facility management,

393
00:22:14,910 --> 00:22:17,140
the kids and disabled
will live comfortably.

394
00:22:17,269 --> 00:22:19,039
I'll renovate the building...

395
00:22:19,039 --> 00:22:20,279
and feed them well.

396
00:22:22,109 --> 00:22:24,250
It's hard,
but I can still manage it.

397
00:22:24,450 --> 00:22:27,279
Why are you stopping me
from doing good deeds?

398
00:22:27,349 --> 00:22:29,890
There are many other good deeds
you can do.

399
00:22:30,849 --> 00:22:31,890
You know,

400
00:22:32,720 --> 00:22:33,990
I'm rich.

401
00:22:34,319 --> 00:22:35,829
I don't need money.

402
00:22:37,529 --> 00:22:38,529
Father.

403
00:22:39,700 --> 00:22:41,930
Why do you always smile
when I put pressure on you?

404
00:22:42,269 --> 00:22:44,000
I'd rather see you get angry.

405
00:22:44,599 --> 00:22:45,670
Hey!

406
00:22:47,500 --> 00:22:49,940
Have some noodles before you go.

407
00:23:01,789 --> 00:23:02,789
One!

408
00:23:03,220 --> 00:23:05,789
- 2.
- 3. Turn your head.

409
00:23:08,289 --> 00:23:09,630
Darn it.

410
00:23:13,630 --> 00:23:15,200
This is Gudam Police Station's
Violent Crimes Team.

411
00:23:15,200 --> 00:23:16,200
I'm Detective Koo Dae Young.

412
00:23:17,670 --> 00:23:19,970
Pardon? A robbery case?

413
00:23:21,099 --> 00:23:22,210
Where is it at?

414
00:23:23,309 --> 00:23:26,880
Sail-dong, 84-1. 2nd floor of
Gguldanji Supermarket.

415
00:23:27,279 --> 00:23:28,480
Okay.

416
00:23:29,109 --> 00:23:31,849
You need to go to the groundbreaking
ceremony of Gudam History Museum.

417
00:23:32,150 --> 00:23:34,380
- I need to get to this place.
- Detective Heo can take care of it.

418
00:23:34,380 --> 00:23:35,420
But he's have ramyeon.

419
00:23:35,420 --> 00:23:37,390
- I'll take care of it.
- You scumbag!

420
00:23:37,720 --> 00:23:38,859
Here.

421
00:23:38,859 --> 00:23:41,890
There must be conscripted policemen
since it's an official event.

422
00:23:41,890 --> 00:23:44,390
Come on. We need one of our guys...

423
00:23:44,390 --> 00:23:46,299
to attend, so that Mr. Hwang
doesn't lose his face.

424
00:23:46,460 --> 00:23:48,200
What face?

425
00:23:48,829 --> 00:23:52,470
A detective isn't some kind of
an honorary ambassador.

426
00:23:53,140 --> 00:23:55,309
- The chief is there.
- I should go then.

427
00:23:56,509 --> 00:23:57,509
There you go.

428
00:23:59,210 --> 00:24:00,210
You can do it!

429
00:24:00,210 --> 00:24:01,410
- See you later, sir.
- See you later, sir.

430
00:24:02,980 --> 00:24:06,220
CEO Hwang Cheol Bum from
Daebum Trading is here with us.

431
00:24:07,079 --> 00:24:08,990
Dear guests on the stage,

432
00:24:08,990 --> 00:24:10,890
please come down.

433
00:24:11,450 --> 00:24:14,359
By turning the first sod,

434
00:24:14,359 --> 00:24:17,390
the construction of
Gudam History Museum will begin.

435
00:24:17,390 --> 00:24:20,329
(Groundbreaking Ceremony
of Gudam History Museum)

436
00:24:25,339 --> 00:24:27,099
Evil business man
Hwang Cheol Bum should explain...

437
00:24:27,099 --> 00:24:30,369
about the Illegal site acquisition.

438
00:24:30,440 --> 00:24:32,380
- He must explain!
- He must explain!

439
00:24:32,380 --> 00:24:34,740
- On the count of three,
- He must explain!

440
00:24:34,740 --> 00:24:37,680
you can throw the dirt to the front.

441
00:24:37,980 --> 00:24:39,980
- You can't cross this line.
- One.

442
00:24:40,380 --> 00:24:41,380
Two.

443
00:24:41,750 --> 00:24:43,819
- Three.
- Run, run!

444
00:24:43,819 --> 00:24:45,420
He must explain about...

445
00:24:46,420 --> 00:24:49,190
Stop Hwang Cheol Bum
from committing crimes!

446
00:24:50,460 --> 00:24:51,490
Let go of me!

447
00:24:52,660 --> 00:24:54,460
Hwang Cheol Bum must step down!

448
00:24:54,660 --> 00:24:56,599
- Hwang Cheol Bum must step down!
- Hwang Cheol Bum must step down!

449
00:24:56,599 --> 00:24:58,700
- Hwang Cheol Bum must step down!
- Hwang Cheol Bum must step down!

450
00:24:58,869 --> 00:25:00,140
Withdraw from your position.

451
00:25:00,500 --> 00:25:01,500
We'll wrap up...

452
00:25:01,569 --> 00:25:05,240
the official ceremony of
today's event.

453
00:25:05,240 --> 00:25:07,640
Captain, where are you going?
What's this?

454
00:25:08,009 --> 00:25:09,049
What? Hey!

455
00:25:09,079 --> 00:25:11,450
- Thanks to all citizens...
- Come here!

456
00:25:11,450 --> 00:25:13,079
- What's going on?
- Gosh!

457
00:25:13,079 --> 00:25:14,519
(Hwang Cheol Bum should explain!)

458
00:25:15,349 --> 00:25:16,750
They're hitting people.

459
00:25:18,720 --> 00:25:20,519
How come the policemen
are just leaving?

460
00:25:21,390 --> 00:25:23,130
Why are they beating people?

461
00:25:24,130 --> 00:25:26,529
Don't cause trouble,

462
00:25:27,160 --> 00:25:30,670
and don't get involved in anything.

463
00:25:31,230 --> 00:25:32,599
- That's...
- Let's just go.

464
00:25:33,039 --> 00:25:34,500
- Pardon?
- Let's go.

465
00:25:34,740 --> 00:25:36,069
But we have to help.

466
00:25:36,140 --> 00:25:37,670
The police will take care of it.
Let's go.

467
00:25:37,670 --> 00:25:39,910
How come the police is evacuating?

468
00:25:39,910 --> 00:25:41,539
- We have to go say hello...
- Father!

469
00:25:41,950 --> 00:25:43,680
Please help us!

470
00:25:43,680 --> 00:25:46,180
We're just poor little lambs.

471
00:25:46,319 --> 00:25:49,119
Father, please don't abandon us.

472
00:25:49,450 --> 00:25:51,190
- Please don't abandon us.
- Let's go.

473
00:25:51,190 --> 00:25:52,890
- Please don't abandon us.
- Let's just go.

474
00:25:52,890 --> 00:25:54,930
- Let's hurry and leave.
- Father has abandoned us!

475
00:25:54,930 --> 00:25:56,160
When did I abandon you?

476
00:25:56,160 --> 00:25:58,930
Dear God!

477
00:26:05,670 --> 00:26:07,339
Why did it have to thunder now?

478
00:26:16,509 --> 00:26:17,779
Darn it.

479
00:26:18,380 --> 00:26:20,619
- Where are you going?
- Get him!

480
00:26:20,619 --> 00:26:22,990
Hey, stop right there!

481
00:26:23,650 --> 00:26:24,789
Wrap it up well.

482
00:26:24,789 --> 00:26:26,420
Don't worry. Safe trip home.

483
00:26:31,190 --> 00:26:33,500
You evil jerk!

484
00:26:35,630 --> 00:26:38,170
- Darn it.
- Let go of me, you jerk.

485
00:26:38,740 --> 00:26:41,269
- Come here, you lunatic.
- Let me go.

486
00:26:41,539 --> 00:26:43,740
- Let me go!
- Stay still.

487
00:26:44,440 --> 00:26:46,279
- Hold him tight.
- Let me go.

488
00:26:46,579 --> 00:26:48,140
Do you want me to break your bone?

489
00:26:48,140 --> 00:26:49,750
- Let go of him.
- Let me go.

490
00:26:49,750 --> 00:26:50,750
Let go of him.

491
00:26:53,619 --> 00:26:54,680
What?

492
00:26:56,490 --> 00:26:57,589
What, you jerk?

493
00:26:59,960 --> 00:27:01,490
What?

494
00:27:38,029 --> 00:27:40,930
(The Fiery Priest)

495
00:27:40,930 --> 00:27:41,930
What's your title?

496
00:27:41,930 --> 00:27:43,569
I'm Detective Koo in Violent Crimes
Team of Gudam Police Station.

497
00:27:43,569 --> 00:27:45,839
How can you just stand and watch
when people are getting beaten?

498
00:27:45,839 --> 00:27:46,839
Sir.

499
00:27:46,839 --> 00:27:49,039
You shouldn't cause
any trouble with this, okay?

500
00:27:50,710 --> 00:27:52,210
This is our new detective.
Say hello.

501
00:27:53,910 --> 00:27:55,109
All right, check it out.

502
00:27:55,109 --> 00:27:56,210
You need to pick your partner.

503
00:27:56,980 --> 00:27:59,349
- Thank you in advance.
- Why am I getting a bad hunch?

504
00:27:59,349 --> 00:28:00,549
I'm sorry to have worried you.

505
00:28:00,549 --> 00:28:03,720
You can just destroy them
like how you always have.

506
00:28:03,720 --> 00:28:05,089
I also love leisure time the most.

507
00:28:05,089 --> 00:28:06,519
Do you really want to die?

508
00:28:06,690 --> 00:28:07,859
I told you not to behave like this.

509
00:28:07,859 --> 00:28:10,190
These guys
are good-for-nothing trash.

510
00:28:10,190 --> 00:28:11,630
I released him with a warning.

511
00:28:11,630 --> 00:28:12,900
You shouldn't have gone
easy on him.

512
00:28:13,099 --> 00:28:14,960
Why are you yelling at me, Father?

513
00:28:15,099 --> 00:28:16,930
Conviction and judgement
come before anything...

514
00:28:16,930 --> 00:28:19,900
Then why are you so judgmental
of everything I say?
